pokedex.py:
    Main Menu that calls all of the actions in 'search.py'
        1- Search a Pokémon by name or ID 
        2- Search information related to a specific type 
        3- Search data of a move
        4- Search data of a hability 
        5- See a random page 
        6- Finish Program

search.py:
    Functions called by the 'pokedex.py'
        search_id_or_name()
            1- If it exist asks about which version of the Pokémon the person wants to see
                1.1- Regional forms
                1.2- Megas and Gigantamax forms
                1.3- Other in or outside battle forms
            2- Write the data of the Pokémon
                2.1- ID and name
                2.2- The type
                2.3- Region and generation of origin
            3- Inside menu to see more options:
                3.1- See the moves the Pokémon can learn
                3.2- Show abilities it can have
                3.3- Show bst (Base Stat Total)
                3.4- Show pokédex descriptions of each game
                3.5- Go back to the Main Menu

        search_type()
            1- Inside menu to see more options:
                1.1- Show all Pokémon that have this type
                1.2- Search pokémon with a secondary type
                1.3- Show moves of this type
                1.4- Show types chart interactions following the example "fire -> grass -> water"
                    1.4.1- Show "2x damage from and to:"
                    1.4.2- Show "1/2x damage from and to:"
                    1.4.3- Show "No damage from and to:"
                1.5- Go back to the Main Menu

        search_move()
            1- Write the data of the move
                1.1- Show effect, short effect, damage class, power, accuracy, pp, type, 
                1.2- If it exist: Show priority and stat changes
            2- Inside menu to see more options:
                2.1- Show Pokémon that can have this move
                2.2- Go back to the Main Menu

        search_ability()
            1- Write the data of the ability
                1.1- Show ability full description
                1.2- Show ability short description
            2- Inside menu to see more options:
                2.1- Show Pokémon that can have this ability
                    2.1.1- Get the ability natturaly
                    2.1.2- Have it as a hidden ability
                2.2- Go back to the Main Menu

        random_page()
            1- Use the 'random' command to chose one of the 4 functions and a random valid link


    Called by the 'search.py' functions:
        1- create_data()
            1.1- Function that creates and access the link required for each search
        2- data_verification()
            2.1- Checks if what the person chooses is possible to not create errors
        3- gen_translate()
            3.1- Switch text "generation-v" to number and region "Unova, generation 5"